Cymbopogon martini var. motia

   [5123.jpg]
    Authority   (Roxb.) J.F. Watson
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5123

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A grass reaching a height of up to 2 m. USES An
   essential oil is extracted from the flowering tops. The oil contains
   95% geraniol and is used for scents in soaps and cosmetics, and as a
   flavoring in tobacco. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. COMMON NAMES Rosha
   grass v. mortia, Palmarosa. FURTHER INF Rosha grass v. mortia grows
   wild in India. It occurs in separated clumps on open, dry hilly areas.
   Mentioned as a useful agroforestry species.

   Sources
   SOURCES (C. martini (Roxb.) Wats. var. mortia)
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 140 [DRA, RAIN, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 102 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 14 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Nair P 1980 pp 314 [DRA, RAIN, FER, USE, LIG]

